<h4 id="1-2-5-audio-description-pre-recorded-aa"><a href="https://www.w3.org/TR/UNDERSTANDING-WCAG20/media-equiv-audio-desc-only.html">1.2.5 Audio description (pre-recorded) (AA)</a></h4><p>Video content like instructional videos must have audio description. This ensures that information communicated visually in the video is available to people who cannot see it.</p>
<h5 id="requirements-what-to-do">Requirements / What to do?</h5>
<ul>
<li>  Video that includes important visual information has audio description;</li>
</ul>
<h5 id="common-mistakes">Common mistakes</h5>
<ul>
<li>  A video includes important visual information but does not have audio description;</li>
<li>  The audio description does not describe important information communicated visually in the video;</li>
<li>  The audio description is not synchronised to complement the audio content of the video.</li>
</ul>
